org.kepler.tagging

Class TagReloadType.TagCacheChange

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.kepler.tagging.TagReloadType
      • org.kepler.tagging.TagReloadType.TagCacheChange
  • Enclosing class:
    TagReloadType

    public static class TagReloadType.TagCacheChange
extends TagReloadType
    TAG_ADDED removes the tag from the auto-completions and adds it to the tag bar. TAG_REMOVED does the reverse. COMPLETE regenerates the tag bar and auto-completions from scratch. TAG_TARGET indicates that a new target of tagging has been selected, perhaps by clicking the canvas or a workflow run; this necessitates an update of both the auto-completions and the tag bar. TAG_ADDED_AND_CLEAR_SEARCH adds the tag to the tag bar and regenerates the auto-completions as if nothing is typed, resulting in all possible auto-completions, minus whatever tags are currently applied to the tag target. SEARCH_STRING updates the auto-completions, removing those that no longer match the search string.
